race.comment: FLICK THE SWITCH (8) was straight back to business first-up, placing here this grade over a touch shorter. Keeps 6x winning rider Faithful, and she's placed 3/3 second-up. Draws awkwardly, but this is winnable with the extra fitness. PRETTY DEVINE (9) had also been racing at Ascot without success and then turned the form around, leading and winning a 52 at York over this distance. That reads well enough, and she tumbles in weight at this level. Draws handy and she can give a big sight. RESONATOR (6) ran a big number, narrowly missing at Ascot at big odds. Compounded badly from the pace in a 72 at Geraldton, following and arrives here for a new barn on an 11-day return. Has the tongue tie on first time, and despite the awkward barrier, he's good enough to keep onside. AVOIDANCE (4) resumed here well in the market but didn't fire. Has the inside barrier and 2kg claim and is proven second-up. Finding his best, the speed-bred gelding would be around the mark.
